Nigeria Idol, a TV reality show for 2020/2021 season 6 audition is set to begin on Sunday Nov.29.
Gotv Nigeria sharing the good news on its twitter @ Gotv Ng said “Nigeria Idol is here.
“if you want to become the next big thing on Nigerian music scene, this is the BEST platform for you.
“Audition opens Nov. 29 and closes Dec. 13.
“Tag anyone who needs this chance.
The reality TV series was aimed to search for young talented individuals in Nigeria with singing competition.
At the commencement of the audition, 30 eligible Nigerians are often selected for the show but only 12 contestants made it to final stage through voting.
The winners goes home with very fantastic prizes including N7.5 million, recording contract with Sony, SUV jeep and a trip to South Africa.
The criteria for interested participants are “to record their 30 seconds video of them singing any song of their choice.
“Upload it to www.Africa magic.tv/Nigerian Idol.
“Must be between 16 and 30 years old to participate.
The show is powered by Multi choice Dstv and Gotv.(NAN)